Objex

  Welcome to the site for the Tal Framework Objex project.
  
  Objex is a framework for creating behaviourally rich persistable business domains.
  Objex strives to put the concepts of Object Orientism OO first and abstract away
  the actual persistence. Objex is not, however, an ORM tool - you will still potentially
  need one of these if using a relational database. Objex simply provides a framework
  where you can describe you objects and define rich behaviour and collaboration
  between the objects, relegating the actual persistence into it's own separate layer 
  where you can concentrate on it separately.
  
  This project is currently incubational and will likely stay that away. It is not
  aimed as a mass open-source framework, although it would be nice if some of the
  ideas in Objex provoked thought and made their way into mainstream frameworks.
  If you disagree and think there is value in Objex itself let me know!
  
